Quadri Aruna has become the first African to hit the semifinal of the World Table Tennis (WTT) Star Contender after the Nigerian defeated China’s Zhou Qihao in straight games 3-0 (11-8, 11-8, 11-7) to join the last four men standing in the Men’s Singles in Doha, Qatar. From the second round where he got a bye as top seed, the Nigerian has been pitched against top Chinese stars but he was able to overcome three of them in a row on his way to the semifinal. Before setting up a quarterfinal tie against Qihao, Aruna had beaten Liu Dingshuo 3-2 (11-6, 9-11, 10-12) in round of 32, Zhao Zihao 3-0 (11-8, 11-8, 11-9) in round of 16 and he continued with another superb win against Qihao to reach the last four of the competition for the first time.   Qatar opens huge sports museum for World Cup     Semi-finalists emerge for Oyo Peller Unity Cup     Ogba slams Eagles on World Cup exit   According to World Table Tennis (WTT), Aruna is touted as one of the title contenders: “Quadri Aruna has been China’s kryptonite in Doha. The Nigerian superstar has added another name to his hit list, defeating Zhou Qihao 3-0 (11-8, 11-8, 11-7) to advance to the Men’s Singles semi-final. “That makes three consecutive Chinese team members which Aruna has sent packing. Most amazingly, he has won the last two matches in straight games. Does this make the Nigerian World No.14 the new favourite to take the title?” Meanwhile, Aruna will  today confront Korea’s Lim Jonghoon in the first semifinal clash of the Men’s Singles on table one in his quest to set a new African record.